description:
Subjects Addressed: (1) “Put on the whole armor of God…For we wrestle against principalities and powers…” Ephesians 6:11-14.
(2)   Principalities and powers represent magistrates, civil leaders, and even judges. Titus 3:1. There are honorable principalities and powers and there are corrupt ones. See Colossians 1:16; Colossians 2:15. (3:20)
(3) Schools that fail to provide adequate housing to transgender students could face lawsuits or the loss of any federal funding they rely on. (13:12)
(4) California Bill effectively eliminates the religious liberty of all universities that integrate spiritual life with their entire educational experience. (14:50)
(5) Canada Supreme Court Legalizes some sex acts with animals. (15:42)
(6) Swiss Tunnel Opening Ceremony Draws Cries of “Satanic.” (18:18)
(7) A religious group is prosecuted for preaching against the Catholic faith, instructing the faithful not to receive sacraments, and persuading others to disapprove of the Pope’s teaching and authority. (23:40)
(8)  The Pope held a meeting at the Vatican with a hundred judges from around the world, fulfilling Daniel 3…Pope Francis explained that the Church is also called on to engage in the field of politics. (26:01)
(9) At “Together 2016” Catholics and Christians unite to change the world with prayer and worship. (32:55)
(10) Pope Francis says that unity between Roman Catholics and the Pan-Orthodox is a must and a good witness for the world to follow. (36:40)
(11) Pope Francis stated that wine is necessary for the [marriage] feast, the unity among all churches and nations. Wine represents false doctrines and policies. Pope Francis blasphemed God by stating that Jesus transformed the Law of Moses into the Gospel.” (38:20)
